{
  "duration": 113.2,
  "language": "en",
  "text": "Excuse me ladies. How did you guys get rich? How did you get rich? Hey, how old were you when you became a millionaire? I was 22 years old. You said 22? 22. 22. How do you now? 34. 34. And how did you get rich? What did you do? I was the founder of an app called Sweat and then we sold. How much did you sell your company for? $400 million. You sold a company for $400 million? Could I interview you for a minute real quick? I go all over the world interviewing the richest people to help the industry. I've seen all your stuff. Where are you from? I'm from Australia. Did you come from a lot of money? Absolutely not. I actually started my parents backyard. Did you have any investors in the company? Did you bootstrap it? We've trapped the whole thing. The entire thing. Yes. $400 million. What's the number one thing that business owners get wrong when they try to sell their company? I mean, I think I did it wrong. I think when you're selling a company you want to be able to sell the company that doesn't have you attached to it. If I could do anything and do it all over again is I would remove myself as part of the company. You want to sell it and be able to celebrate and relax, but for me it wasn't relaxing. They call that the key man risk. That's right. That's why they say that Disney's the best business because Mickey Mouse isn't in the negotiations. That's exactly right. I love that. So there's the truth to that? Absolutely there is. Now you made a lot of millions in your career. How does somebody make their money work for them? Don't put all your eggs in one basket. The first thing that ever made me money that was so excited that I bought was a petrol station. A gas station? A petrol station. A gas station. You bought a gas station? Yeah and I was like, wow, out of all the millions of dollars it's so cool to see rent coming in from a gas station. Like just diversifying your world. Because one day the internet might shut off and it'll all be gone. Were there any days early on that you didn't think that it was going to work out? There were days that I would literally be found in a ball in the corner of my gym crying because I got overwhelmed. So for somebody that may feel like they're at rock bottom, they're dealing with a ton of pressure right now. What would be your message to them? The greatest piece of advice I've ever received is someone said, you know that you are under no obligation to be the same person you were yesterday. And I think that is really strong in the fact that you can make a change. If you have a passion, go for it. You've got amazing advice. Thank you so much. Thank you so much for your time. I appreciate that. I connect with all the millionaires and billionaires I interview. Can I get your contact? Of course.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.9,
      "text": "Excuse me ladies. How did you guys get rich?"
    },
    {
      "start": 2.3,
      "end": 5.5,
      "text": "How did you get rich? Hey, how old were you when you became a millionaire?"
    },
    {
      "start": 5.7,
      "end": 9.6,
      "text": "I was 22 years old. You said 22? 22. 22. How do you now?"
    },
    {
      "start": 10.6,
      "end": 12.8,
      "text": "34. 34. And how did you get rich? What did you do?"
    },
    {
      "start": 13.0,
      "end": 17.7,
      "text": "I was the founder of an app called Sweat and then we sold. How much did you sell your company for?"
    },
    {
      "start": 17.9,
      "end": 21.3,
      "text": "$400 million. You sold a company for $400 million? Could I interview you for a minute real quick?"
    },
    {
      "start": 21.3,
      "end": 24.6,
      "text": "I go all over the world interviewing the richest people to help the industry. I've seen all your stuff."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.8,
      "end": 28.0,
      "text": "Where are you from? I'm from Australia. Did you come from a lot of money?"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.7,
      "end": 32.3,
      "text": "Absolutely not. I actually started my parents backyard. Did you have any investors in the company?"
    },
    {
      "start": 32.4,
      "end": 35.6,
      "text": "Did you bootstrap it? We've trapped the whole thing. The entire thing. Yes. $400 million."
    },
    {
      "start": 36.3,
      "end": 39.6,
      "text": "What's the number one thing that business owners get wrong when they try to sell their company?"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.8,
      "end": 40.8,
      "text": "I mean, I think I did it wrong."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.9,
      "end": 45.2,
      "text": "I think when you're selling a company you want to be able to sell the company that doesn't have you attached to it."
    },
    {
      "start": 45.2,
      "end": 49.5,
      "text": "If I could do anything and do it all over again is I would remove myself as part of the company."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.7,
      "end": 53.1,
      "text": "You want to sell it and be able to celebrate and relax, but for me it wasn't relaxing."
    },
    {
      "start": 53.3,
      "end": 55.0,
      "text": "They call that the key man risk. That's right."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.0,
      "end": 58.5,
      "text": "That's why they say that Disney's the best business because Mickey Mouse isn't in the negotiations."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.6,
      "end": 61.2,
      "text": "That's exactly right. I love that."
    },
    {
      "start": 61.3,
      "end": 63.3,
      "text": "So there's the truth to that? Absolutely there is."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.4,
      "end": 66.6,
      "text": "Now you made a lot of millions in your career. How does somebody make their money work for them?"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.7,
      "end": 70.3,
      "text": "Don't put all your eggs in one basket. The first thing that ever made me money that was so excited"
    },
    {
      "start": 70.3,
      "end": 73.7,
      "text": "that I bought was a petrol station. A gas station? A petrol station. A gas station."
    },
    {
      "start": 73.8,
      "end": 76.8,
      "text": "You bought a gas station? Yeah and I was like, wow, out of all the millions of dollars"
    },
    {
      "start": 76.8,
      "end": 81.1,
      "text": "it's so cool to see rent coming in from a gas station. Like just diversifying your world."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.3,
      "end": 83.1,
      "text": "Because one day the internet might shut off and it'll all be gone."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.1,
      "end": 85.7,
      "text": "Were there any days early on that you didn't think that it was going to work out?"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.9,
      "end": 89.8,
      "text": "There were days that I would literally be found in a ball in the corner of my gym crying because"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.8,
      "end": 92.5,
      "text": "I got overwhelmed. So for somebody that may feel like they're at rock bottom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.7,
      "end": 95.4,
      "text": "they're dealing with a ton of pressure right now. What would be your message to them?"
    },
    {
      "start": 95.5,
      "end": 98.0,
      "text": "The greatest piece of advice I've ever received is someone said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 98.1,
      "end": 101.0,
      "text": "you know that you are under no obligation to be the same person you were yesterday."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.1,
      "end": 104.8,
      "text": "And I think that is really strong in the fact that you can make a change."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.9,
      "end": 107.4,
      "text": "If you have a passion, go for it. You've got amazing advice."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.6,
      "end": 109.3,
      "text": "Thank you so much. Thank you so much for your time. I appreciate that."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.5,
      "end": 112.2,
      "text": "I connect with all the millionaires and billionaires I interview. Can I get your contact?"
    },
    {
      "start": 112.2,
      "end": 112.7,
      "text": "Of course."
    }
  ],
